summary: Completed comprehensive testing of VoltFit fitness tracking app. Backend APIs show 94.4% success rate with only minor AI parsing issue. Frontend authentication, navigation, and UI/UX working perfectly with correct VoltFit theme implementation.

minor_bugs.issue: AI returns calories/protein as strings (e.g., '580 kcal') but backend expects integers
minor_bugs.impact: Meal plan generation fails with validation error
minor_bugs.error_details: 2 validation errors for MealPlan - calories: Input should be a valid integer, unable to parse string as an integer [type=int_parsing, input_value='580 kcal']

passed_tests: User registration and login flow with JWT authentication
Dashboard displaying user stats and navigation
Personal goal creation, tracking, and progress updates
Group goal creation, joining, and real-time chat messaging
Weight tracking with manual entry and chart visualization
Navigation between all pages (Landing, Login, Register, Dashboard, Meals, Goals, Groups, Weight, Profile)
Profile page with fitness integration infrastructure placeholders
Responsive design and VoltFit theme implementation (dark mode, volt green accents)
Protected route authentication (redirects to login when session expires)
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix AI meal plan generation parsing issue: Modify /api/meals/generate endpoint to extract numeric values from AI responses like '580 kcal' -> 580 and '25g' -> 25 before saving to database. The AI integration is working but response parsing needs improvement.
